cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SD 

This paper deals with the problem of mining social annotations to learn folksonomies, which is a task that falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the issue of user diversity and how it affects the quality of annotations, which is related to the field of Social Computing (cs.SI). The proposed framework involves identifying experts and leveraging their knowledge, which can be seen as a form of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Machine Learning (cs.CY). Finally, the evaluation of the approach involves analyzing the quality of the learned folksonomies, which can be considered as a form of Data Mining (cs.SD).
